Furshlugginer: one of several words made up by the original writers of MAD Magazine, "Furshlugginer" is an adjective with as many possible meanings as the user deems necessary. Often used in a negative sense (ex: "You Furshlugginer robot! Can't you do anything right?"), it came into almost-popular usage in the late Seventies and early Eighties by those seeking a more gonzo state of conciousness.